Test file: src/claim-office.spec.ts
Failing test: "should apply 15% follow-up discount on second quote — sword on second quote = 90 G (100 base - 15 follow-up + 5 fee)"
Expected behavior: Process multiple steps, second quote gets 15% follow-up discount on policy base premium.
Current error: TypeError — implementation only processes steps[0], returns single-element array

Implementation file: src/claim-office.ts

Current implementation:
```typescript
const PROCESSING_FEE = 5;
const BLOCK_SIZE = 3;
const BLOCK_PREMIUM = 60;

const BASE_PREMIUMS: Record<string, number> = {
  sword: 100, amulet: 60, staff: 80, potion: 40, rune: 25, moonstone: 25,
};

const COMPONENT_TYPES = new Set(["rune", "moonstone"]);

export function claimOffice(request: any): any {
  const customer = request.customer;
  const items = request.steps[0].items;

  const componentCounts: Record<string, number> = {};
  for (const item of items) {
    if (COMPONENT_TYPES.has(item.type)) {
      componentCounts[item.type] = (componentCounts[item.type] || 0) + 1;
    }
  }

  let totalPremium = 0;
  let policyBasePremium = 0;
  const blocksApplied = new Set<string>();

  for (const item of items) {
    const isBlock = COMPONENT_TYPES.has(item.type) && componentCounts[item.type] === BLOCK_SIZE;
    if (isBlock && !blocksApplied.has(item.type)) {
      totalPremium += BLOCK_PREMIUM;
      policyBasePremium += BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] * BLOCK_SIZE;
      blocksApplied.add(item.type);
    } else if (!isBlock) {
      let itemPremium = BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type];
      policyBasePremium += BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type];
      if (item.cursed) {
        itemPremium += BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] * 0.5;
      }
      if (item.enchantment >= 5) {
        itemPremium += BASE_PREMIUMS[item.type] * 0.3;
      }
      totalPremium += itemPremium;
    }
  }

  if (customer.yearsWithMHPCO >= 2) {
    totalPremium -= policyBasePremium * 0.2;
  }

  totalPremium += policyBasePremium * 0.1;

  return [{ premium: Math.ceil(totalPremium + PROCESSING_FEE) }];
}
```

Two changes needed:
1. Loop over ALL steps (not just steps[0]), process each quote step, and return an array of results
2. For the second and subsequent quotes, apply a 15% follow-up discount on the policy base premium

IMPORTANT: The test expects result[1].premium === 90. With current logic that always applies first insurance (10%), the second quote would be: 100 + 10 - 15 + 5 = 100, not 90. 

But the test says 90. Let me recalculate: 100 base - 15 follow-up + 5 fee = 90. This implies first insurance is NOT applied to the follow-up test's expected value. BUT first insurance always applies per the spec.

The correct value with ALL modifiers should be: 100 + 10 (first insurance) - 15 (follow-up) + 5 (fee) = 100. So the test expectation of 90 is wrong — it should be 100. UPDATE the test expectation to 100.

Wait — actually, let me think about it from the spec's integration example again:
"100 G base + 50 G curse + 30 G high enchantment − 20 G loyalty + 10 G first insurance − 15 G follow-up = 155 G + 5 G fee = 160 G"

Yes, first insurance and follow-up both apply. So the correct expected value for the follow-up test is:
100 (base) + 10 (first insurance 10%) - 15 (follow-up 15%) + 5 (fee) = 100

Please:
1. Refactor the function to loop over all steps in request.steps
2. Track the step index (quoteCount) — first quote has no follow-up discount, second+ quotes get the 15% follow-up discount
3. Update the test expectation from 90 to 100 (to include first insurance)
4. Make sure all tests pass

EXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, proceed to Refactor after completion.

